Samson Folarin The remains of a Lebanese have been found in a septic tank in his house on Bombay Crescent, in the Apapa area of Lagos State. The PUNCH learnt that the victim was murdered by his domestic workers. It was gathered that the victim had travelled to Abuja and asked the workers to look after the house. However, upon his return, he discovered that some hoodlums had taken over the apartment, which led to an argument. He was reportedly killed and his remains hid in the septic tank. The Police Public Relations Officer, DSP Bala Elkana, confirmed the incident. He said, “He was murdered by his domestic servants. Our men are closing in on them.”